The filter's transfer function is \( H(\omega) = \frac{1 - e^{-j\omega\tau}}{j\omega} \), which corresponds to the Fourier transform of a rectangular pulse of width \(\tau\).  
The output is the convolution of the input impulse \( I\delta(t) \) with the impulse response \( h(t) = u(t) - u(t-\tau) \), resulting in \( v_o(t) = I[u(t) - u(t-\tau)] \).  

\boxed{H}
